headline: Corrections
abstract: Corrections that appeared in print on Saturday, Jan. 18, 2020.
lead_paragraph: An article on Friday about a report that said the White House violated a law by withholding aid to Ukraine described incorrectly the legislative history of the Impoundment Control Act. The bill was signed into law in 1974 by President Richard M. Nixon after being passed in Congress; it is not the case that the bill was passed over the veto of Mr. Nixon.
